          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-25 09:16:44" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:ἐπισκοπέω&lt;SDBG:ἐπισκοπέω:000000&gt;}[a] ‘to take care of,’ {D:35.39}) the position of one who has responsibility for the care of someone</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>position of responsibility</Gloss>
                <Gloss>position of oversight</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though in some contexts ἐπισκοπή has been regarded traditionally as a position of authority, in reality the focus is upon the responsibility for caring for others, and in the context of {S:04400102000040} the reference is clearly to the responsibility for caring for the church (see {D:53.69}).</Comments>
